{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4173d45c-d3ad-48ef-862e-e8c364488d08","content":"Good news — with .NET 10 SDK, `dotnet test` natively speaks the Microsoft.Testing.Platform protocol. You **no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`**. That property was a bridge for .NET 9 and earlier SDKs; .NET 10 makes it a no-op.\n\nYour project already has the two things that *are* still required:\n\n- `<EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>` — builds the test project as an MTP executable\n- `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` — required by the runner\n\nSo the fix is simply removing the obsolete property:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01WgX18UxQey9XijdHa4WyHN","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete MTP property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Bzt1igdjKJkxpCe9pjLsMa","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-9bccf8a92de441498c6280382088d4b7/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-9bccf8a92de441498c6280382088d4b7/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"ffc328c2-739d-4c55-adfb-1857d78d1e3d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK and using MSTest with Microsoft.Testing.Platform. They want to know:\n\n1. How to set up native MTP support in .NET 10's `dotnet test`\n2. Whether they still need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. The `dotnet test` command in .NET 10 uses MTP by default. So they can remove the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property.\n\n\nThe `EnableMSTestRunner` property is still required to activate the MTP-based runner for MSTest, and since their project already has `OutputType` set to `Exe`, they have the necessary configuration in place. I'll update their project file to remove the obsolete property and confirm what they need to keep.","outputTokens":635,"requestId":"4C1D:30490E:D57BEE:10A2938:6A012A9D"},"id":"552fa82d-96ee-4432-a32b-c336e787ce85","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:02:31.633Z","parentId":"3e0f1102-9857-4a00-b34c-f50c291ca710"}
